                    </labels>
                <created>Mon, 15 Apr 2013 20:33:45 +0000</created>
                <updated>Fri, 2 Feb 2018 06:33:48 +0000</updated>
                            <resolved>Fri, 2 Feb 2018 06:33:48 +0000</resolved>
                                                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>7</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="218534" author="utopiabound" created="Thu, 18 Jan 2018 16:54:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve pushed the lustre wireshark plugins upstream, so that they won&apos;t live in our repo any longer.  See &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6353&quot; title=&quot;Push Wireshark Support Upstream&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-6353&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-6353&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="181128" author="tgeerdes" created="Wed, 18 Jan 2017 15:16:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, I&apos;d try including ubuntu in wsconfig.sh.  Create your branch from the master branch of the lustre-release repo when creating the review.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="179251" author="tarebax" created="Fri, 30 Dec 2016 18:18:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Since we now have ubuntu builder, shouldn&apos;t we update wsconfig.sh to include ubuntu? or should we stop building it altogether since it&apos;s (wireshark) included in b_ieel  as per Frank&apos;s?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="166936" author="tgeerdes" created="Thu, 22 Sep 2016 16:58:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We currently have ubuntu in the builder list and after &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/22074/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/22074/&lt;/a&gt; what actions does DCO need to take for wireshark build support?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="142722" author="jlevi" created="Thu, 18 Feb 2016 15:09:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Reopening into TEI backlog&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="120049" author="agarcia" created="Wed, 1 Jul 2015 15:34:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a more general ticket for wireshark support.  Putting as low priority until we get time to address&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="120048" author="agarcia" created="Wed, 1 Jul 2015 15:31:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Per Triage, we don&apos;t compile against Ubuntu and we don&apos;t have Ubuntu in our build environment.  If this is needed in the future, someone can open up a ticket and we&apos;ll plan to address then&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="93105" author="heckes" created="Wed, 3 Sep 2014 12:51:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Andi:&lt;br/&gt;
The work was postponed last year. I don&apos;t whether there a necessity to finish the tickets (TEI- 82, 133, 356). &lt;br/&gt;
I think wireshark is part of b_ieel now (if I remember correctly from release notes), so the tickets mentioned above might can be closed by &apos;won&apos;t fix&apos;.? &lt;br/&gt;
Otherwise the change was close to land last year actually. Only problem was that the build environment for Ubuntu wasn&apos;t complete and therefore wireshark couldn&apos;t be build for this distro.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="57722" author="utopiabound" created="Mon, 6 May 2013 13:49:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;To build via just typing &quot;make&quot; I believe I fixed with my patch on &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3135&quot; title=&quot;Wireshark plugins Makefile not working&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3135&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3135&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  I was building via just &quot;make install&quot;, but on Fedora 17. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
